column57:
Each of the items below describes things college students sometimes ask of other people. Please imagine that you are in each situation. 

 

 

 
You ask your parents for help in deciding what programs to apply to.

 

 How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want to help you?
column58: I would expect that they would want to help me.
column59:
You approach a close friend to talk after doing or saying something that seriously upset him/her.




How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your friend would want to talk with you?
column60: I would expect that he/she would want to talk with me to try to work things  out.
column61:
After graduation, you can't find a job and ask your parents if you can live at home for a while.
 

 

How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want you to come home?
column62: I would expect I would be welcome at home.
column63:
You call your boyfriend/girlfriend after a bitter argument and tell him/her you want to see him/her.
 

 

How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your boyfriend/girlfriend would want to see you?
column64: I would expect that he/she would want to see me.
column65:
You ask your parents to come to an occasion important to you.
 


How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want to come?
column66: I would expect that my parents would want to come.
column67:

How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your friend would do this favor?
column68: I would expect that he/she would willingly do this favor for me.

How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your boyfriend/girlfriend would say yes?
